   <h1>RE: [VB] Problems already... Dowel pin dilemma</h1>
   <b>Ronnie Feitelson &lt;Ronnie_at_OldVolks_dot_com&gt;</b><br/>
   <i>2000-07-05 23:58:02+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>Only on a crank drilled for 8 dowels is the 1 pin offset, on a standerd 4
hole crank and flywheel it will go on any which way, to many times have I
seen flywheels and/or cranks drilled backwards for the 8 dowel and went they
went to put the flywheel on there was no way it would fit, bummer. So look
at the end of your crank and you will notice that 1 dowel will be offset and
a little closer to the rest, hopefully the wasted dowels are the ones from
the additional 4 dowels and not 1 of the originals, if thats the case your
in good shap, if not ouch. You could take the flywheel to a shop and have
them drill just the 1 offset for you, this is not the best way but will
work, then you'll only have to worry about oil leaks through the extra dowel
hole. Another fix and I have had this done before is that they can drill the
crank while still in the case for oversize dowels, just set it up in a drill
press or prefeally a milling machine and drill out to oversize, then do the
same to the flywheel, just another way to save a crank.

ronnie

ps. if you ever looked at a crank from Barret or most of the other VW rag
parts whores most of there cranks have had the dowels plugged and redrilled,
they can get them cheaper that way, those people buy all the junk cranks
from the same place I get my good ones from, but I do pay a lot more then
the cheapo places, but I do get good cranks, no dowel plugs, no welded
journels, like most of the cheap cranks out there. The way it works is if I
turn in a standard crank with a wasted journel, they will charge me for a
weld, oh no i say no welded journels take it to 20 under if you have to, if
I have oblonged or wasted dowels they will charge for a plug and drill,
again oh no I say, these cranks I end up giving them and when they repair
them they go to the vw rag whores who have no morals. NQ can contest to
that, (his welded heads) another subject I won't go into.

